He was batty.

513
01:12:27,760 --> 01:12:31,239
He asked for it.
It was an accident.

514
01:12:33,800 --> 01:12:36,507
Oh, God,
I want to go home.

515
01:12:37,770 --> 01:12:40,275
Ow!

516
01:12:40,238 --> 01:12:43,682
<i>Ow! Ow!</i>

517
01:12:46,643 --> 01:12:48,757
<i>Take him away!</i>

518
01:13:03,428 --> 01:13:05,613
Tomorrow, I'll hunt again.

519
01:13:06,899 --> 01:13:09,748
Then we'll leave another head
for the beast.

520
01:13:17,577 --> 01:13:21,055
Some of you will stay
and defend the gate.

521
01:13:22,113 --> 01:13:25,105
The beast may try
and come in.

522
01:13:30,956 --> 01:13:33,141
Remember how he crawled ?

523
01:13:33,124 --> 01:13:36,354
<i>He came disguised.</i>

524
01:13:36,294 --> 01:13:39,358
<i>The beast may try and come,</i>

525
01:13:39,296 --> 01:13:42,525
<i>even though we gave him
the head of our kill to eat.</i>

526
01:13:42,467 --> 01:13:44,794
<i>So watch and be careful.</i>

527
01:13:48,241 --> 01:13:50,948
But didn't we--
Didn't we--

528
01:13:52,709 --> 01:13:55,867
<i>No. How could we kill it ?</i>

529
01:14:00,752 --> 01:14:04,860
He told us.
The beast was disguised.

530
01:14:06,559 --> 01:14:10,835
Tomorrow, when we get meat,
we'll have a feast.

531
01:14:12,931 --> 01:14:15,224
- Chief?
- Yes, Bill ?

532
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:18,264
<i>What'll we use
to light the fire ?</i>

533
01:14:18,202 --> 01:14:21,812
We'll get fire
from the others.

534
01:14:23,641 --> 01:14:25,720
We've got to get
out of this.

535
01:14:25,709 --> 01:14:27,728
What do you mean ?

536
01:14:27,713 --> 01:14:30,562
Get rescued.

537
01:14:30,515 --> 01:14:33,056
I mean it.

538
01:14:33,017 --> 01:14:36,983
If we don't get out of here soon,
we'll be barmy.

539
01:14:36,887 --> 01:14:39,915
- Around the bend.
- Crackers.

540
01:14:48,301 --> 01:14:51,423
Have you written a letter
to your auntie lately ?

541
01:14:51,369 --> 01:14:53,697
I don't know
where she is now,

542
01:14:53,670 --> 01:14:57,743
and I haven't got
an envelope or a stamp,

543
01:14:57,640 --> 01:15:01,154
and there isn't
a pillar box or a postman.

544
01:15:03,148 --> 01:15:06,033
I haven't said
anything very funny.

545
01:15:10,155 --> 01:15:16,247
<i>Piggy-y-y-y!</i>

546
01:15:16,061 --> 01:15:18,245
<i>Piggy!</i>

547
01:15:20,131 --> 01:15:22,531
Don't make a sound.

548
01:15:22,499 --> 01:15:25,099
<i>We're going
to get you, Piggy.</i>

549
01:15:27,070 --> 01:15:29,397
<i>Piggy ?</i>

550
01:15:29,376 --> 01:15:32,476
<i>Where are you, Piggy ?</i>

551
01:15:32,412 --> 01:15:35,784
<i>- We've come to get you.</i>

552
01:15:46,022 --> 01:15:49,573
Ow! Ow! Ow!

553
01:16:03,907 --> 01:16:06,614
<i>Piggy, you've changed!</i>

554
01:16:06,576 --> 01:16:09,178
Piggy!

555
01:17:20,318 --> 01:17:23,832
I just take the conch
to say this.

556
01:17:23,756 --> 01:17:27,438
I can't see
without my glasses,

557
01:17:27,360 --> 01:17:30,387
<i>and I got to get them back.</i>

558
01:17:30,327 --> 01:17:33,320
<i>What are we going to do ?</i>

559
01:17:54,919 --> 01:17:57,104
Hey! Who goes there ?

560
01:17:57,087 --> 01:18:01,089
Stop being silly!
You can see who I am!

561
01:18:16,574 --> 01:18:19,115
I'm calling an assembly!

562
01:18:19,076 --> 01:18:21,510
<i>Boo! Boo!</i>

563
01:18:29,855 --> 01:18:32,635
Don't leave me, Ralph!

564
01:18:35,325 --> 01:18:38,519
You sit down
and wait for me. Here.

565
01:18:44,901 --> 01:18:47,442
What do you want ?

566
01:18:47,405 --> 01:18:52,001
<i>Go away, Ralph!
You keep to your end.</i>

567
01:18:51,875 --> 01:18:56,709
This is my end and my tribe.
You have to leave me alone.

568
01:18:56,580 --> 01:19:00,712
<i>You took Piggy's specs.
You've got to give them back.</i>

569
01:19:00,619 --> 01:19:03,683
Got to ? Who says ?

570
01:19:03,621 --> 01:19:06,814
I say!
That was a dirty trick.

571
01:19:06,757 --> 01:19:09,820
We would have given you fire
if you asked for it.

572
01:19:09,761 --> 01:19:12,789
But you didn't.
You came sneaking up like a thief.

573
01:19:12,728 --> 01:19:15,792
- Say that again!
- Thief! Thief!

574
01:19:15,733 --> 01:19:17,952
Who's a thief?

575
01:19:17,935 --> 01:19:19,954
You are!

576
01:19:21,107 --> 01:19:25,488
Ralph!
Remember what we came for.

577
01:19:25,377 --> 01:19:28,262
The fire. My specs.

578
01:19:28,211 --> 01:19:31,441
Don't you see ? There may be
a ship out there or a plane!

579
01:19:39,124 --> 01:19:41,832
- Grab 'em!
-Jack!

580
01:19:41,792 --> 01:19:44,226
<i>Tie 'em up!</i>

581
01:19:46,430 --> 01:19:49,528
See ?
They do what I want.

582
01:19:49,469 --> 01:19:53,187
You're a beast and a swine
and a bloody, bloody thief!

583
01:19:56,240 --> 01:19:58,781
<i>Boo! Boo!</i>

584
01:19:58,743 --> 01:20:01,556
<i>Go, Jack! Go!</i>

585
01:20:22,099 --> 01:20:24,700
<i>Let me speak!</i>

586
01:20:24,670 --> 01:20:27,210
I've got the conch!

587
01:20:42,956 --> 01:20:45,556
Which is it better to be ?

588
01:20:45,524 --> 01:20:50,013
A pack of panting savages
like you are...

589
01:20:51,027 --> 01:20:53,391
or sensible like Ralph is ?

590
01:20:53,365 --> 01:20:56,738
- Which is better?

591
01:20:56,665 --> 01:21:01,118
<i>To have rules and agree,
or to hunt and kill?</i>


